paragraphs.text:
%md
Introduction
===

The purpose of this demonstration is to show how to automatically ingest files from NPPES and load them into Solr

Steps
===
1. Pull down the current NPPES data file and unpack it
2. Do some preprocessing with Python to clean up those files
3. Upload the files to HDFS
4. Generate a Hive schema using the first row as column headers and create external tables in Hive
5. Copy from Hive/Files to Hive/Solr

paragraphs.text:
%sh
rm -rf ~/nppes
mkdir ~/nppes
cd ~/nppes
wget -O nppes.zip "http://download.cms.gov/nppes/NPPES_Data_Dissemination_Feb_2016.zip"
mkdir raw
unzip -d raw nppes.zip

%sh
export BASE=/user/zeppelin/nppes

hdfs dfs -rm -r -skipTrash ${BASE}
hdfs dfs -mkdir ${BASE}

cd ~/nppes/raw

fn=npidata_20050523-20160207.csv
hdfs dfs -mkdir -p ${BASE}/current/${fn%.csv}/
hdfs dfs -put ${fn} ${BASE}/current/${fn%.csv}/

%sql
